code: import pandas as pd import re import html from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split from sklearn.metrics import f1_score from sklearn.preprocessing import MultiLabelBinarizer import fasttext # Load and clean training data train = pd.read_csv("./input/train.csv", usecols=["Title", "Body", "Tags"]) train["Tags"] = train["Tags"].fillna("") train["Title"] = train["Title"].fillna("") train["Body"] = train["Body"].fillna("") # Select top tags and filter invalid rows all_tags = train["Tags"].str.split().explode() top_tags = all_tags.value_counts().head(500).index.tolist() def clean_text(text): text = html.unescape(text) text = re.sub(r"<.*?>", " ", text) # Fix regex with raw string text = re.sub(r"\s+", " ", text).strip().lower() return " ".join(text.split()[:1000]) train["text"] = (train["Title"] + " " + train["Body"]).apply(clean_text) train["Tags"] = train["Tags"].apply( lambda x: " ".join(tag for tag in x.split() if tag in top_tags) ) train = train[train["Tags"] != ""] # Remove rows with no tags # Format for FastText and split data train_ft = train.apply( lambda row: " ".join([f"__label__{tag}" for tag in row["Tags"].split()]) + " " + row["text"], axis=1, ) train_data, valid_data = train_test_split(train_ft, test_size=0.2, random_state=42) # Save formatted data train_data.to_csv("fasttext_train.txt", index=False, header=False) valid_data.to_csv("fasttext_valid.txt", index=False, header=False) # Train model model = fasttext.train_supervised( input="fasttext_train.txt", lr=0.2, epoch=30, wordNgrams=2, thread=16, verbose=2 ) # Validate valid_texts = [] valid_true = [] for line in valid_data: parts = line.split() labels = [p[len("__label__") :] for p in parts if p.startswith("__label__")] valid_true.append(labels) valid_texts.append(" ".join(parts[len(labels) :])) pred_labels = [model.predict(text, k=5)[0] for text in valid_texts] pred_labels = [[l.replace("__label__", "") for l in lst] for lst in pred_labels] mlb = MultiLabelBinarizer(classes=top_tags) y_true = mlb.fit_transform(valid_true) y_pred = mlb.transform(pred_labels) f1 = f1_score(y_true, y_pred, average="samples") print(f"Validation F1-Score: {f1:.4f}") # Predict test set test = pd.read_csv("./input/test.csv", usecols=["Id", "Title", "Body"]) test["Title"] = test["Title"].fillna("") test["Body"] = test["Body"].fillna("") test["text"] = (test["Title"] + " " + test["Body"]).apply(clean_text) full_model = fasttext.train_supervised( input="fasttext_train.txt", lr=0.2, epoch=30, wordNgrams=2, thread=16, verbose=2 ) test_preds = [full_model.predict(txt, k=5)[0] for txt in test["text"]] test["Tags"] = [ " ".join([l.replace("__label__", "") for l in lst]) for lst in test_preds ] test[["Id", "Tags"]].to_csv("./submission/submission.csv", index=False)
